Liberation.

lib·er·a·tion
/ˌlibəˈrāSH(ə)n/

noun
1. the act of setting someone free from imprisonment, slavery, or oppression; release.

Sometimes the most powerful forms of imprisonment, slavery and oppression are created by attachments to our identity and the relationships we create through them: relationships to people, places, careers, experiences… where once an action or form might have served to help us express, over time it  can be that it is no longer expression or creation. It is conforming to what has been .

Question: if there’s something you’ve always wanted to do for yourself but choose not to for whatever reason, is that love? Or fear? 

Having been blessed with a very full and forgiving head of hair,  I’ve been super lazy about brushing it, or fixing it. This can take on the appearance of “care free “ and non vanity. But  considering that whatever shape my hair was in it would somehow come out looking wild but stylish, was my attitude toward it truly carefree? Or identification WITH  being carefree ?
I woke up on this  particular morning, prepping for my annualish haircut, and caught myself thinking, “ hm…maybe it’s time for simple bangs to help cover the ever deepening wrinkles in my forehead and to cast a bit of shadow over my healing right eye.” Carefree???

… So I #shaved it off. #inspired by my #daughter @siennAnemone, and her  #bravery in choosing to experience herself free of what she called “hiding behind” her hair… I dove right in and will simply be present with what unfolds internally. 

In the least,  it’s an experiment in #nonAttachment and I will have given myself the experience I’ve long been curious about.

#shave #bald #shavedHead #liberation #freedom #goforit #brave #bravetheshave. #beautifulHair #bare

In Spiritual circles it is said that to manifest what we truly desire, we must 1st
BE the truth of who we are then 
DO from that truthful state of being. The result is we 
HAVE what makes us truly happy as opposed to what we think will bring us happiness. 
Last night I sat down to acknowledge & write out my desires for 2023, including expressing through the written word. But I found myself thinking, “Wait! After the rain stops let’s go get a new journal & pen to start fresh.” So I put it off. This morning as the rain continued on, my first knowing was, “You want to write? WRITE! You have everything you need in this moment to do what you want to do as an expression of who you really are. Why wait?” 
  Then it occurred to me that over 1.5 yrs ago I moved to northern Cali, secured a beautiful loft over a recording studio solely to complete the book I had started 4 years earlier. Have I touched it? No. Why? Because I had to get the loft set up just right. Then the producer downstairs needed a hand with a song. The property needed help: chickens fed, rocks moved, weeds pulled.  Ah, hell, I may as well throw in my need for the right pillow, coffee, & summer dress.
What did I actually need? Paper, a pen, and my computer. Did I have those things? Yes. All along.
We have these dreams of expressing ourselves freely in truth, whether it be through music, engineering, baking, whatever. But we find distractions under the label of duty, organization, education, anything. There are umpteen million reasons for you NOT to create from your true state of being but only 1 reason TO: You. Aren’t you worth it?
 As a co-creation with the perfect energetic patterns of Source, your expression from this state is always to the highest good of all because you’re bridging the human and the divine.
Humanity deserves it.
I deserve it.
You deserve it.
So in 2023 my desire and commitment is to live in accordance with Be-Do-Have by 1st realizing that in some way, I 
HAVE everything I need to 
DO what I want to do as an expression of my true
BE ingness.

It’s not about achieving. It’s about expressing from our truest state of Being.

BE Do Have…Have Do BE in #2023!  #happynewyear #inspire

A message for a loved one that I feel is perfect for all of us on the first day of 2023: 
  Beautiful Human, 
You are a being of such magnificence. Power, willfulness and intelligence, yes. But also there is an innocence, a sensitivity, and childlike wonder that have been buried , the embracing of which will help harmonize the totality of you. This is what will bring you true happiness.

It is not unusual for such imbalances. It is the way of being human. After all, we incarnate to remember our divinity which in and of itself is a perfect yet unique patterning, a fractal of GOD.

This world cannot safely hold let  alone acknowledge or understand this expression, though it is impacted massively in realms unseen by its exquisiteness.

Go boldly albeit privately into this year of 2023 never doubting your true nature which is that of LOVE. And enjoy the evolution of attunement  that requires no efforting, only its honoring through a carving out of space  and time for such attunement to occur.

I love you. 
Virenia  #Beauty #LOVE #2023 #happiness #joyful #divinemasculine #divinefeminine #harmonize #friendship #famly

#HighSchool friends Ahhhh❣️Life is wonderfully curious at times. It brings so many unexpected turns. Sometimes those turns take you far away from where you once were, both literally and figuratively. To embrace the evolution takes courage. To allow everyone, including those you have loved deeply to evolve differently and potentially away from you takes even more.
We have loved each other enough to allow truth to unfold:) The temptation is to return as you once were because it is what is known… the invitation is to be the truth of what you have become and allow others to do the same. Is this not unconditional love?  Lucky for me, the hearts of these two beautiful souls have only opened over the years. Thank you Criss and Russ for sharing the afternoon and your beautiful essence  with me once again ❤️❤️❤️

Something very profound occured during my fast. It’s taking me some time to integrate, this the pause in posting. Something #profound occurred during my #fast. Having been such a powerful focuser of #energy in my life, (some might call that #overachieving;) the way I would #manifest was largely through my willfulness, my #commitment, my #drive . On one level, It got things done. But the #universe has been inviting me into a much more powerful place that includes more #miracle than muscle… the subtle energies of creation.  It requires relinquishing the personal power I have known to joining the power of all that is. It is terrifying. It is #curious. It is profoundly #beautiful and healing. It is something I don’t fully understand  yet have known forever. Thus is the joining of the human and the #divine, that which we are in truth.
I love you all madly. I am #grateful to be on this journey with you.

#Change is inevitable. #Transformation  is a choice. 
-Virenia 
In my 20s 30s and 40s, this is how energy moved through me: powerfully, demonstratively, dynamically. I look back and applaud the fearlessness of moving through life with such curiosity, fearlessness  and commitment. .  What I’m learning now is that to transform is not simply to intentionally step. It is to be aware in every moment what is happening internally: in my #heart, my #mind, my emotional-energetic-spiritual bodies and allow them to show me where, when  and how life is inviting me to #evolve by energetically JOINING  the miracles, the #divine perfection that is already in motion on my  behalf. Even if what’s being shown to me  is unmeasured, unappreciated, uncategorized by familial, personal (programmed?) societal standards, I must trust. I then step.
It took great courage to trust the laws of Newtonian physics that allowed me to run up that wall and do a back flip. (Thanks to my stunt gurus:)
But boy does that pale in comparison to the faith and devotion it requires to #Surrender into #Grace, trusting the more subtle yet powerful energy of GOD: the Quantum Divine. Is this the true process of transformation? What do you think?.. What do feel???

Finally my hair is long enough to be given some shape . Up to this point it was like a chia pet with a wild streak.

Honestly it was an interesting experiment in self love and self compassion as my hair went through its phases. (Swipe to see) But one of the best things was realizing I could move through my day anonymously. WHAT??? I’m not a big star running from paparazzi any longer but I never even realized that I rarely went through a day without someone recognizing me from one show or another. Not a big deal. People are usually kind. But anonymity… wow. I never realized the pressure I placed on myself to show up “on point” in every public moment of my day. And I wondered what self inflicted pressures others place upon themselves. Please share your experience!

#selflove #selfcompassion #public #hair

Walking this beautiful sunset yesterday I was captured by how beautiful the clouds reflected the colors of the sunset.  In that moment I felt deep appreciation for the various forms of human beings, on their  paths with their unique desires, successes, failures, joys and fears. I felt unified with all.

But That night I  awoke around 3 am sobbing with one hand on my lower abdomen. I became intensely aware of the expectations and hopes my body was holding regarding certain relationships . These expectations are like  an energetic noose keeping me bound to an “idea” of future with little regard for the truth of the  present.  And it is only in the present moment that we become  aware of endless possibilities we could never have even fathomed.

“As I release these old expectations, I free myself to create, to express as the Divine creator I am. “

We are all aspects of the Divine . How do you wish to express, to create? 

Let us lean  into our worthiness of such divine desire.  #Desire #sunset #divine #expectations #freedom #abundance #creativity

I’ve known for some time that the universe mirrors things back to us in various forms: relationships, circumstances, happenstances, synchronicities.

But when I heard it in these words, “What you show up as…” it helped the message clarify and sink in more deeply. 

Many of us can relate to being a giver, a kind, compassionate, thoughtful human. But when it’s constantly at the expense of our own well being, does that mean we’re showing up as martyrs, In servitude rather than in service? And if so, is it any wonder that we are surrounded by those in need who are unwilling, unable to acknowledge or give back to us in equal measure? 

It’s my belief that at the core, those beautiful characteristics are our very nature. Our species’ perpetuation and ability to thrive depend upon it. 

Yet there exists such a fine and fragile line that lies between service and servitude. Can we add our light to the sum of all that is if we run our own energy down so low, that we ourselves are now diminished?

What are we showing up as?
 #selflove #authentic #universe #lawofattraction #manifestation #kindness #goodness #compassion
